## <a id='new-features'></a> New Features

Healthwatch v2.2 includes the following major features:

* **[Feature Improvement]** Allow scaling of Grafana, Mysql, and Mysql Proxy instances to 0.

* **[Feature]** Healthwatch now directly scrapes Bosh Director metrics for Ops Manager versions 2.10.10+. Exposed on the
  Director Health dashboard

* **[Feature]** System at a Glance dashboard - a new landing page when logging into Grafana that displays an overview
  of system health.

* **[Feature]** For new installations, the Alerting routing rules have been prefilled with a sensible default value.

* **[Feature]** When Healthwatch is installed alongside TAS, now supports fully automatic configuration of a Grafana
  route instead of manual provisioning.

* **[Feature]** When Healthwatch is installed alongside TAS or TKGI, now supports fully automatic configuration of
Grafana UAA authentication, instead of manual configuration.

* **[Feature]** Metrics probe_success and probe_duration_seconds are now emitted into the firehose from the SVM
  Forwarder.

* **[Feature Improvement]** TAS SLI Canary App health check timeout has been increased to 5 minutes to reduce
false negatives.

* **[Feature Improvement]** Healthwatch dashboards showing Canary App data will only show the currently configured
Canary Apps, no longer displaying outdated data.

* **[Bug Fix]** Diego App Chunks Remaining underlying math calculation fixed.

* **[Bug Fix]** Changed Ops Manager Canary URL to fix source of log bloat in <code>/home/tempest-web/uaa/tomcat</code>
  on Ops Manager VM

* **[Bug Fix]** Fixed TAS SLI Login test displaying success instead of failure on timeout.

* **[Feature Improvement]** TKGI Cluster Discovery will automatically configure itself by default if TKGI is present.





